You are driving your junker of a car down main street, heading home after a long day at work.  Your eyes burn from staring at the computer screen.  Your head hurts.  The cell phone in the empty passenger seat begins to ring and you look away from the road to see who it is.  Oh no.  Not her...you reach over to pick it up.  What a perfect end to a perfect day, you think sarcastically.  Suddenly, you hear the scream of tires and a blast from a car's horn.  Your heart leaps into your throat as adrenaline sears through your veins.  But you are too late.  The world is abruptly filled with noise, light, pain...your life evaporates like the agony you felt for only a moment.

You open your eyes slowly.  Blinking, you turn your head first right, then left.  What the...  What has happened?  How did you get here?  You slowly get to your feet, the muscles in your back and legs reacting slugishly.  You feel dizzy...why is the ground so far away?  You have never felt so confused.  What is this place?

In order to return home, you feel like you need to explore this land.  Be especially observant toward the creatures and items that you come across and don't forget to read the signs...some are there for excellent reasons.
