You are in a Barren Wasteland.
You can see a Na'shan and a Sandy Sign.
You can go south, east or west.
You hesitantly take in the strange new surroundings.  What new hell is this?  As far as you can see to the north, east, and west, there is nothing but what appears to be a flat wasteland.  The sun beats down on you, merciless and everpresent.  You start cautiously forward and suddenly you see a black robed person appear in front of you.
What are you going to do?
> ask man about help

> ask man about help
"You do look lost.  You'll never get very far on foot...but Sky Elves frown on giving things away without a trade.  Let's see...You have some Giant Spider silk?  I could use that on a new bowstring...Here," he gives you a White Flute, "you'll never get very far on foot in the Sky Realm.  Play this when you are in need.  And it seems like you are reasonably helpless.  Take this," he also gives you a gold coin.  "Just remember this help when the day for battle arises."

After trading with you, Na'shan's eyes lighten and he steps backwards...off of the ravine's edge!  You hurry forward just in time to see what looks like a cross between a giant eagle and a lion swoop under him.  The strange elf-man-creature flies off on the bird.  WHAT IS GOING ON??
What are you going to do?
> east

> east

You are at the an Edge of Eastern Ravine.
You can see a Hell Bird and a Hellish Sign.
You can go west or Fly.
You reach the edge of a gaping ravine that drops suddenly into a black chasm.  It is over thirty feet wide and absolutely impossible to cross.
What are you going to do?
> play flute

> play flute
A beautiful, wild music drifts up from the flute.
The bird lowers himself to the ground, tilting his back.  Is it just you, or does he looks like he wants you to get on?  Perhaps you should have another LOOK at the situation...
What are you going to do?
