You are in a Castle of Shadows.
You can see Natalia Nezrai and Phoenix.
You can go west.
After crossing a long and pale bridge over an expansive lake, you enter a castle built from black stone.  Poenix stops beside you, sword at the ready, and you look over the strange new surroundings with weary interest.  The walls of this room are carved from ebony stone and there is a blood red carpet running up its center.  While the guards have allowed you to pass through the rest of the castle unharmed, you now are confronted by two soldiers with white skulls on their helms.  Seated on a thrown directly in front of you is a tall looking woman in a black dress with dark purple sides.  She regards you under a heavily lidded gaze with angled, elvish eyes.
What are you going to do?

The woman on the thrown sighs, her eyes reflecting a dark, complex realm of thought as she says, "You are Lost, are you not?  I can tell from your eyes, if not your physical form.  The eyes are the mirror to the soul.  Is that not what your people say?"

"Your response matters little," she continues when you say nothing.  "I am Natalia Nezrai of the Center Realm.  Welcome to my home, the Castle of Shadows. Its name arises from the darkness that plagues us all, thou of the Lost."

"You are a lying fool, Nazrai!"  Phoenix suddenly shouts, his words echoing across the dark walls.  You glance nervously at him, but the woman seems amused.

"Lying is part of my beauty, dear one," she purrs.  "Guards."

The guards seize Phoenix and haul him away, leaving you alone with the strange woman.

"Where was I?  Ah, yes.  Do you know where you are?  Who you are?  No?" she barely pauses for you to answer.  "I didn't think so.  You are a Wood Elf from Krippler's Forest, one that we captured only weeks ago to undergo my...experiments," she chuckles over the word.  "It takes a weak soul to lose a body.  It takes time.  Your name was Lyra of Shade.  But it is your name now that I am interested in."

 "You see, my magicians stumbled across Soul Splicing purely by chance.  What is it?  I suppose you of all people deserve to know.  My magicians were conducting experiments for me many years ago to create a more...docile subject.  Personality modifications, so to speak.  But it was then that they discovered an entirely different realm of what it is to be human.  Souls."

Nezrai smiles slightly as she watches you.

"Religious leaders attempted to convince me for centuries that living things contained souls, but I never put any stock in the notion.  Not until my head magician, Lucian Dravkoni, managed to extract one.  The process is more complicated than you could understand, so I will simplify matters by saying that we remove and contain a creature's soul, allowing room for a new one to enter.  This seemed fairly pointless.  Until we discovered the Other World."

"Not unlike the discovery of Energy, this has changed everything.  We accidentally captured a soul from a different world.  Each soul is different.  Each world is different.  Tell me, dear one, are you from a world that believes in this?  This...paralell universe, so to speak?"
You can TELL NEZRAI ABOUT your WORLD or you can ATTACK NEZRAI.
> attack nezrai

> attack nezrai
You run at Nezrai, but before you can cross the distance, a guard appears at her side and stabs you through your heart................
What are you going to do?

............beep......beep................beep..............................For a long while, all that you hear is this soft sound.  Then, slowly, your eyes drift open.

You are in a Hospital Room.
You can see a Nurse.
The room is quiet except for the soft beeping of the heart monitor attatched to your right index finger.  Tubes are running from a bandage on your forearm to an IV stand at your bedside.  You are on your back and despite your efforts, you cannot seem to move.  The room is painfully bright.  You blink.  What has happened?  Was that all a dream?  Where are you?
> ask nurse about who

> ask nurse about who
"So glad to see that you are awake.  I am your nurse.  You have been in a coma for days now.  I'll get your doctor..." she leaves the room.
What are you going to do?
You wait.  And as you wait you wonder.

What is real?

Thanks for playing LOST IN THE SHADOWS OF TIME, based on my independant novel of the same name.  If you would like to learn what happens next in this story, leave a comment and I'll see about continuing the series.  If you have any further questions or comments, please contact me at: krilliams@gmail.com .  I look forward to your feedback.

NOTE: This is my first attempt at creating a text-based adventure.  I appologize for any errors or inconsistencies with the gaming format.
